			<h3>Talks</h3>
			
			<p> Here are some talks on this subject, with publically available abstracts and/or videos.</p>
			
			<ul>
			
				<li>Margaret Burnett's <a href="https://youtu.be/Sj3MkCWwllc">GenderMag talk</a> ITU Copenhagen is now available on youtube. This talk was presented in November 2015, and represents the latest version of GenderMag.</li>
				
				<li>See the <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=uhOBd34q2kM)">Google Tech Talk about GenderMag</a> (presented May 11, 2015).</li>

				<li>Here is a <a href="http://www.interaction-design.org/encyclopedia/end-user_development.html">handful of mini-interviews done in Rome, June 2011</a>, with Margaret Burnett and <a href="http://web.engr.oregonstate.edu/~cscaffid/">Chris Scaffidi</a> for our new encyclopedia article, about End-User Programming, End-User Software Engineering, and Gender.</li>

				<li>Margaret Burnett gave a <a href="http://icpc2011.cs.usask.ca/conf_site/Schedule.html">keynote at ICPC</a> late in June 2011 on this topic.</li>

				<li>Margaret Burnett gave a <a href="http://www.ppig.org/workshops/ppig-2010-22nd-annual-workshop/programme">keynote at PPIG 2010</a> early in September 2010 on this topic.</li>

				<li>Here is a June 2009 <a href="http://channel9.msdn.com/shows/WM_IN/Margaret-Burnett-Gender-and-Software/">Microsoft Channel 9 interview on Gender and Software</a> with Margaret Burnett.</li>

				<li>Laura Beckwith and Margaret Burnett gave a talk in September 2006 summarizing the findings at that time, at <a href="http://web.engr.oregonstate.edu/~burnett/MicrosoftResearchCambridge-2006talk/talk.htm">Microsoft Research Cambridge, on gender issues in end-user programming</a>.</li> 

			</ul>

			
